The paper proposes a new method for knowledge graph embedding that utilizes additional information about entities, specifically their neighbors. This involves both semantic and topological features, which suggests that the paper could fall under categories such as artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and databases (cs.DB).
